<subSubSection id="C353652ADB29D86DFF7114B3FB094E42" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF636A1DB29D86DFF7114B3FB094E42" blockId="7.[151,1436,1482,1617]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">
Male genital characters are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D22DB29D86DFD4214B2FCB64D8B" authorityName="Lindberg" authorityYear="1929" box="[676,789,1482,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Dicraneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB3DB29D86DFD4214B2FCB64D8B" box="[676,789,1482,1508]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">V. oculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but this species is distinguishable by the pygofer having a dorsal process, the central lobe of the connective absent, preatrium of the aedeagus obviously short, and shaft thicker and less curved. Body length: 
<specimenCount id="9D4FFD28DB29D86DFDD9176BFDF74E43" box="[575,596,1554,1580]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
<quantity id="4CB19B44DB29D86DFDBD176BFD464E43" box="[603,741,1554,1581]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.35" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="4.35" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="4.2">4.2‒4.5 mm</quantity>
; 
<specimenCount id="9D4FFD28DB29D86DFD16176BFCA64E43" box="[752,773,1554,1580]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
<quantity id="4CB19B44DB29D86DFCEA176BFC304E43" box="[780,915,1554,1581]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.3" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="4.4" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="4.3">4.3‒4.5 mm</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD84B50DB29D86DFC47176BFB3E4E42" author="Dworakowska, I." box="[929,1181,1554,1581]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" pagination="97 - 139" refId="ref6637" refString="Dworakowska, I. (1993 b) Fusiplata Ahmed and some other Dikraneurini (Insects, Auchenorrhyncha, Cicadellidae: Typhlocybinae). Entomologische Abhandlungen Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde Dresden, 55 (7), 97 - 139." type="journal article" year="1993">Dworakowska, 1993b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
